etymology.description: 爪(爪) (zhǎo, "hands") + 角(角) (jiǎo, phonetic) + 女(女) (nǚ, "woman") -> later 母(母) (mǔ, "mother") + 中(中) (zhōng, "middle") + 女(女, "daughter")
etymology.interpretation: The character originally combined elements representing hands, a phonetic component, and a woman, suggesting a conceptual or functional relationship. Over time, it evolved to an ideogrammic compound involving maternal and female aspects. However, the exact meaning remains uncertain, possibly symbolizing family or familial duties.
